de.akuz.osynce.macro.serial.payloads
Class PersonalData

java.lang.Object
  de.akuz.osynce.macro.serial.payloads.AbstractPayload
      de.akuz.osynce.macro.serial.payloads.AbstractFixedLengthPayload
          de.akuz.osynce.macro.serial.payloads.PersonalData
All Implemented Interfaces:
Payload
public class PersonalData
extends AbstractFixedLengthPayload

This class represents the payload needed to be send to set the personal data of the user in the cycle computer. All values should be set here, since everything not set defaults to zero and is written to the device.

Author:
Till Klocke

setUpperHeartRateLimit

public void setUpperHeartRateLimit(int limit)
Sets the upper heart rate limit. This limit must be below 240 and above the lower heart rate limit. This limit should be set first.

Parameters:
limit - heart rate in beats per minute

setLowerHeartRateLimit

public void setLowerHeartRateLimit(int limit)
Sets the lower heart rate limit. This limit must be above 30 and below the upper heart rate limit. The upper heart rate limit should be set first.

Parameters:
limit - heart rate in beats per minute

setUserFlags

public void setUserFlags(int flags)
- User flag: Bit 0: set if bike2 selected Bit 1: set if user sex is female Bit 2: set if speed scale is m/h Bit 3: set if weight scale is kg Bit 4: set if temperature scale is degree F Bit 5: set if user go to use 24 hour format Bit 6/7 : Data rate setting 00b = 5sec 01b = 10 sec 10b = 20sec

Parameters:
flags -

setDataRate

public void setDataRate(int rate)
Set data rate to 5, 10 or 20 seconds. This method simply divides the given integer by 10 and shifts all bits by six to get the necessary flag. No Exception will be thrown if given rate is not 5,10 or 20, but strange things could happen.

Parameters:
rate -
